column5: Hi all, got into crappie at binbrook conservation and been hooked ever since, but instead of paying fees and driving to binbrook I live right on the grand and can get my canoe inbetween York and Cayuga. So my question is, is there many crappie in this area? I wouldn't mind eating some either. I've heard there's some in the Cayuga area, but can't remember where I heard it. Any tips also greatly appreciated! Thanks!
I've caught some down that way off creek mouths on small minnows under floats.
